Mourners on Tuesday gathered at Citam Church, Nairobi, to pay their last respects to retired Justice Daniel Aganyanya. Family, relatives and friends gathered together to celebrate the retired Justice, who was know as the no-nonsense judge. Among those who attended the memorial were lawyers, judges among the Court of Appeal president Justice William Ouko and senior counsel Pheroze Nowrojee. Aganyanya will be buried at his home in Kisasi village on Saturday.